Editing tools (wysiwyg and markup) create links within confluence that do not specify the space by default. These links break when content is displayed in a different page and/or space (include macro, reporting plugin, attachments macro, etc.). 

In 2.5.7 links within a space do not have the space specified. The link breaks when content is displayed in another space. 2.6.2 seems to do this better. 

The real problem is with images and attachments. These always break as links created within ythe containing page do not typically specify the space and the page containing the attchment. When content is displayed, listed, or collated elsewhere, these unspecific attachement links refer to attachments in the display context rather than the context of the original page, where they are actually located.

